quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  19,59,But the generations who succeeded them abandoned the Salah and started following their lusts; so they will soon face the consequences of their deviation
  19,60,"However, those who repent, become believers and do good deeds, will be admitted to Paradise and will not be wronged in the least"
  19,61,"They will be granted the Gardens of Eden which the Merciful has promised to His servants, even though they have not seen them, and His promise shall be fulfilled"
  19,62,"There they will hear no nonsense, but only the words of peace; and they will be provided their sustenance day and night"
  19,63,Such is the Paradise which We shall give as an inheritance to those of Our Servants who lead a pious life
  19,64,"The angel Gabriel who brought this revelation after a long interval said: \"We do not descend from heaven except by the command of your Lord; to Him belongs whatever is before us and whatever is behind us and all that lies in between. Your Lord is never forgetful"
  19,65,"He is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, and of all that lies in between, so worship Him, be steadfast in His worship. Do you know any other being with the qualities like Him"
  19,66,"Man says: \"What! Once I am dead, shall I be raised to life again"
  19,67,Does not man remember that We created him before out of nothing
  19,68,"By your Lord, We will call them to account in the company of all their Satans and set them on their knees around the Fire of Hell"
  19,69,then from every sect We will certainly drag out its stoutest rebels against the Compassionate (Allah)
  19,70,Certainly We know best who deserves most to be burned therein
  19,71,"There is not a single one of you, who shall not pass over it, this absolute decree of your Lord is unavoidable"
  19,72,then We will deliver those who were pious and leave the wrongdoers therein humbled on their knees
  19,73,"When Our Clear Revelations are recited to them the unbelievers say to the believer: \"Which one, of the two of us, have fine dwelling and better companions"
  19,74,"Don’t they see, how many generations have We destroyed before them, who were far greater in riches and in splendor"
  19,75,"Tell them: \"Anyone who has gone astray, the Compassionate (Allah) prolongs his respite and extends an opportunity until they see about which they were warned; - be it a worldly scourge or the Hour of Doom - then they will realize whose is the worst dwelling and whose are the weak companions"
  19,76,"In fact, Allah increases in guidance those who seek guidance; everlasting are only the good deeds, which are the best in the sight of your Lord to earn you a better reward and yield you the best fruit"
  19,77,"Have you noticed the words of that person who rejects Our Revelations yet boasts: \"I shall always be given wealth and children"
  19,78,Has he gained knowledge of the Unseen or has he been awarded a contract by the Compassionate (Allah)
  19,79,By no means! We write down what he says and We will make his punishment long and terrible
  19,80,"We will inherit all that he boasts of, and he will come back to Us all alone leaving all these things behind"
  19,81,"They have taken other deities for worship besides Allah, so that they should be a source of strength to them"
  19,82,By no means! Those very deities will renounce their worship and turn against them
  19,83,Don’t you see that We have sent down to the unbelievers Satans who incite them against the Truth
  19,84,"Therefore be not in haste against them, their days are numbered"
  19,85,The Day will surely come when We will gather the righteous like honored guests before the Compassionate (Allah)
  19,86,and drive the criminals to Hell like thirsty cattle are driven to water
  19,87,None shall have the power to intercede except the one who may receive the sanction of the Compassionate (Allah)
  19,88,"Those who say: \"The Compassionate (God) has begotten a son"
  19,89,certainly preach such a monstrous falsehood
  19,90,"that the very Heavens might crack, the earth might cleave asunder and the mountains might crumble to pieces"
  19,91,at their ascribing a son to the Compassionate (God)
  19,92,It is not befitting to the Compassionate (God) that He should beget a son
  19,93,There is none in the heavens and in the earth but must come to the Compassionate (Allah) in full submission
  19,94,He has a comprehensive knowledge and has kept strict count of all His creatures
  19,95,and every one of them will come to Him individually on the Day of Resurrection
  19,96,Surely the Beneficent will bring about love for those who believe and do good deeds
  19,97,We have made this Qur’an easy in your own language so that you may give good news to the righteous and warn the headstrong contentious folk
  19,98,"How many generations have We destroyed before them! Can you see any of them, or hear even a sound of them"